On Wednesday, September 03, 2003, at 06:01AM, scott lyons <slyons(-at-)netrover.com> wrote:

>> You need a grade 10.9 bolt
>
>list,
>
>for what it is worth, i just put new cv boots on my VW thing and the kit
>came with grade 12.9 bolts. not sure if this is standard as i was surprised
>they were that hard. the only other grade 12.9 fasteners on a bus are the
>head studs. the boot kits were german made by "te-gu-fa".

The original bolts are 10.9 and that's all that's required to handle the torque from the stock engine. That size/style fastener is more commonly found in the 12.9 grade which is why your kit probably came with them.

